[We post this simply to pass on the information that Harvey Artsob and his
group and heading appropriate surveillance mechanisms. The writing of this
report needed more editing than I gave it but I particularly enjoyed the
"chickens acting as sitting ducks" phrase. Keep writing like that and the
reporter will get egg on her face.
As for the final statement, that "the findings could be misleading because
the test used to detect the virus is new, very sensitive and experimental",
I hope that is a misquote. CDC has reported that West Nile virus RNA was
detected in overwintering mosquitoes in the Borough of Queens, New York
City, and my understanding is that they later isolated the virus. Virus
isolation is not misleading. - Mod. CHC]
